sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1114109
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Bicistronic design RBS 12, MoClo Format with BC fusion sites
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Traci Haddock
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the MoClo formatted part of a bicistronic design ribosomal binding site 8 with BC fusion sites. This is a Level 0 MoClo part with flanking sites B on the 5' side and site C on the 3' side of the part. The fusion site letters refer to 4bp fusion sites: A = GGAG; B = TACT; C = AATG; D = AGGT; E = GCTT; F = CGCT; G = TGCC; H = ACTA. Backbone is a modified version of pSB1C3 with added SpeI site in front of gene, BsaI sites flanking, and 4bp fusion sites. See BBa_K783055.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This is the MoClo formatted part of a bicistronic design ribosomal binding site 8 with BC fusion sites. sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part was cloned off a BCD template from Sonya Iverson. Sonya Iverson based her designs for her BCD2 part off of a paper published by Mutalik, et al.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1401008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Tandem Promoter pBad-pTet
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kathleen Lewis
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This tandem promoter was created using the MoClo assembly method. This is a Level 0 MoClo part with flanking sites A on the 5' side and site B on the 3' side of the part. The fusion site letters refer to 4bp fusion sites: A = GGAG; B = TACT; C = AATG; D = AGGT; E = GCTT; F = CGCT; G = TGCC; H = ACTA. The promoter is induced by atc and arabinose. The characterization data will be updated before the jamboree.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We looked through the literature and decided to attach the two promoters without any extra sequence between them
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This was formed using BBa_I13453 and BBa_R0040

The fusion site letters refer to 4bp fusion sites: A = GGAG; B = TACT; C = AATG; D = AGGT; E = GCTT; F = CGCT; G = TGCC; H = ACTA. Backbone is a modified version of pSB1C3 with added SpeI site in front of gene, BsaI sites flanking, and 4bp fusion sites. See BBa_K783055.
